column2: dd$text[grep("Ross", dd$text)]
"I mean, didn't you think you were just gonna meet somone, fall in love- and that'd be it? ..Ross?"
"Ross, what's the matter?"
"Um... Ross?"
"Oh Ross, you're so great."
"And Ross."
"Oh, Ross..."
"Oh Ross, you're so great!"
"Bzzzz.... I love you, Ross."
"Can you believe what a jerk Ross was being?"

"Well, well, well, hop back in bucko, cause I got four sixes! I won! I actually won! Oh my God! Y'know what? I think I'm gonna make a little Ross pile. I think that one was Ross's, and I thinkohthat one was Ross's. Yes! : Well, I have got your money, and you'll never see it..."
"Oh God, Ross, I cannot do this."
"Oh God... Okay. Alright. Alright. Okay. Ross, please don't hate me."
"Ross, I'm doing everything that I can, I've got everybody looking for him, and I- Oh! Who is it?"
"Ross, you don't know that."

"Ross, I said I'm sorry like a million times. What do you want me to do? You want me to break my foot too? Okay, I'm gonna break my foot, right here. Ow!! Oh! Oh my God, oh my God! There, are you happy now?!"
"Ross."
"Ross."
"Ross!"
"Oh, Ross, c'mon. It's my fault, I almost lost your..."
"Please. If she said to you, \"Ross, I want you on this couch, right here, right now,\" what would you say?"
"Oooooooooh. Oh, that's nice. Oh, oh. Huh, Ross!"
"Ross?"
"Ross?"
"Rossy, Rossy."
"Oh, Ross, relax. It's probably like two dollars for the first contraction, and then fifty cents for each additional contraction."
"Ross? All this time? Well, I've got to talk to him."
"Ross! Excuse me, pardon me, excuse me...."
"I don't know. I don't know... I thought about it all the way there, and I thought about it all the way back... and, uh, oh, you guys, y'know, it's Ross. Y'know what I mean? I mean, it's Ross."
"Uh, yeah. Uh, Monica, y'know, honey, I've been thinking about it and I've decided thisthis whole Ross thing, it's just not a good idea."
"Ross, it's too hard."
"Ross, you're like my best friend."
"Airport, airport. Ross, not alone, Julie, arm around her. Cramp, cramp."

"Ok, ok, ok. How did this happen to me? How did this happen to me? A week ago, two weeks ago, I was fine. Ross was just Ross, just this guy. Now he's Rrrooossss, oh, this really great guy that I can't have."

"Um, ok, uh, oh god, um, when you and uh Ross first started going out, it was really hard for me, um, for many reasons, which I'm not gonna bore you with now, but um, I just, I see how happy he is, you know, and how good you guys are together, and um, Monica's always saying how nice you are, and god I hate it when she's right."
"For Ross, Ross, Ross."
"Ross, you have to understand that your nice thing makes us feel this big."
"Oh, look at me, look at me. Oh, I'm on a date with a really great guy, all I can think about is Ross and his cat and his... Julie. I just want to get over him. gosh, why can't I do that?"

"Ross, hi, it's Rachel. I'm just calling to say that um, everything's fine and I'm really happy for you and your cat who, by the way, I think you should name Michael. And, you know, ya see there I'm thinking of names so obviously, I am over you. I am over you and that, my friend, is what they call closure."
"Oh my God. Oh my God Ross, no, hang up the phone, give me the phone Ross, give me the phone, give me the phone, give me the. . ."
"Alright, I got it Ross."
"Alright, fine, you go ahead and you do that, alright Ross."
"Ross kissed me."
"Did uh, Ross call?"

"Why didn't he call? He's gonna stay with Julie, isn't he? He's gonna stay with her and she's going to be all, \"Hi, I'm Julie, Ross picked me, and we're gonna to get married, have a lot of kids and dig up stuff together.\""
"Ross, Chandler wrote something about me on his computer and he won't let me see."
"What is this? Ross, what is this?"
"When somebody does not buzz you in, Ross, that means go away. That doesn't mean please climb up the fire escape."

"No, you don't, Ross. Imagine the worst things you think about yourself. Now, how would you feel if the one person that you trusted the most in the world not only thinks them too, but actually uses them as reasons not to be with you."
"Oh, well, that's, that's mighty big of you, Ross. I said don't go!"
"Wha... forget it Ross, no, I am not gonna stand here and make a list of. . ."
"Yeah, and you know what? You're right, I do feel better, thank you Ross."
"Oh, I know, I'm sorry you guys. You're just gonna have to get used to the fact that I will not be dating Ross."
"This is Joey, and Phoebe, and this is Chandler, and you remember Ross."
"Oh, Ross, you had to, I mean, he was humping everything in sight. I mean, I have a Malibu Barbi that will no longer be wearing white to her wedding."
"OK, Ross, listen to me, I am not yours to save."
"Ross, there is no us, OK."
"NO but Ross. We are never gonna happen, OK. Accept that."
"I'm sorry. Oh God, I'm sorry, it's just that when you moved your hands down to my butt, it was like woah, Ross's hands are on my butt. Sorry."
"Yes, but you can not tell Ross 'cause I want to surprise him."
"Yes I do, it's just that Ross is. . ."
"Is Ross here?"
"Oh God. Ross, OK, if you care about me at all, you will get the pie out of the man's hood."
"Ross, Ross, please listen to me. Ross, you are so much better for me than Paolo ever was. I mean you care about me, you're loving, you make me laugh."
"God, Ross, look, what you and I have is special, all Paolo and I ever had was..."
"Ok, Ross, try to hear me. Ok, I, hey, I'm not gonna lie to you. Ok, it was good with Paolo."
"Yeah well, Ross just made plans for the whole century."
"Ross, you have planned out the next 20 years of our lives, we've been dating for six weeks."
"Ok, Ross, Ross, ok listen, what we have is amazing."
"Ok Ross, just so you know, calling it a poopie diaper doesn't make this process any cuter."
"I'm sorry, what did you just say? Did you just say hi? Oh my God, Ross, Ross, Ben just said 'Hi'."
"Oh Ross, would you stop, you got me, I'm dating you."
"Ross, you know what..."
"Ross, I didn't think it would that big of a deal."
"Okay, Ross, Phoebe is my girlfriend, okay, we tell each other everything. You know, I mean, come on, guys do the same thing, I mean, what about all that locker room stuff."
"That is so sad. Your missing out on so much, Ross. I mean, the bonding and the sharing, you know. And-and knowing that someone else is going through the same thing you are."
"Ross, that was a Halloween costume, unless you would like me to go to this thing as Little Bo Peep."
"Yes, Ross."
"Ross's what?"
"Ross, you are so pathetic. Why can't your son just play with his doll?"
"Yeah, 'cause that's why you won't get Isabella Rosselini, geography."
"Ross, it took you ten years to finally admit you liked me."
"Honey, he's about to go hit on Isabella Rosselini. I'm just sorry we don't got popcorn."
"Ross, my father doesn't hate you."
"You remember Ross."
"Yeah, actually Daddy Ross is allergic to lobster."
"Yes, it bothers me Ross, but y'know if he was a regular at the coffee house, I'd be serving him sneezers."
"So. Ross, I've bugged him about this a million times, he's not gonna change."
"Ross, tonight was about the two of you getting along. Oh, would you just see my chiropractor, already."
"All right, look, here's the bottom line Ross, this is fixable, if we act fast, okay. So, I'll invite him to brunch tomorrow and you can make nice."
"Okay, look, Ross, I realise that my Father is difficult, but that's why you have got to be the bigger man here."
"Okay, well can't you just try it one more time Ross? For me? For me?"
"Okay. Okay honey, he's fine, he's fine, let's just put him down. Come here, Ben. See that's a good boy. How could you do that to him!! Ross trusted me, what is he going to say?!"
"Let's do it! Ross?"
"Ross!"
"No, it's not gonna be okay Ross, tomorrow is my last day, and I don't have a lead. Okay, y'know what, I'm just gonna, I'm just gonna call Gunther and I'm gonna tell him, I'm not quitting."
"I didn't have to, because I was wearing my 'I heart Ross' sandwich board and ringing my bell."
"Ow! Ross!!"
"All right Ross!! I get it!!"
"Oh, please, Ross it was so obvious! It was like you were marking your territory. I mean you might have well have just come in and peed all around my desk!"
"Ross!"
"Oh my God!!! Ross!!"
"Nodded off!! Ross you were snoring. My father's boat didn't make that much noise when it hit rocks!"
"Ross honey, this is very nice, but, but I-I got a crisis."
"Ross you're not listening to me, I don't have time to stop."
"Hey, Ross!!! I told you I don't!"
"You had no right coming down to my office Ross. You do not bring a picnic basket to somebody's work! Unless maybe they were a park ranger!"
"Wh, Ross what do you want from me? You want me, you want me to quit my job so you can feel like you have a girlfriend?"

"Ross do you realise this is the first time in my life I'm doing something I actually care about. This is the first time in my life I'm doing something that I'm actually good at. I mean. if you don't get that..."
"Oh my God. I cannot keep having this same fight over and over again, Ross, no, you're, you're, you're making this too hard."
"Oh my God. I cannot keep having this same fight with you Ross! Look, urrgh, maybe we should take a break."
"Yeah, but it's okay, because when Ross left Mark came over."
"Hi, it's me. I've been trying to reach you all night. I feel awful. Please, Ross, you gotta know there is nothing between me and Mark. This whole break-up thing is just stupid."
"Ross, you had sex with another woman!"
"Come on Ross! You said you wanted to talk about it, let's talk about it!! How was she?"
"No Ross!! Don't! You can't just kiss me and think you're gonna make it all go away, okay? It doesn't work that way. It doesn't just make it better. Okay?"

"No. I can't, you're a totally different person to me now. I used to think of you as somebody that would never, ever hurt me, ever. God, and now I just can't stop picturing with her, I can't, it doesn't matter what you say, or what you do, Ross. It's just changed, everything. Forever."
"No! No, I am not getting in a car with Ross, we will just have to live here!"
"Why would you even want to come Ross? You're a horrible skier."
"Y'know Ross why don't you put that on your answering machine!"
"Ross, I watched you get hypnotised in Atlantic City."

"I mean I think I'd say no to anybody right now. Oh, but it was so strange. I mean I'm standing there with this charming, cute guy, who's asking me to go out with him, which I'm allowed to do, and I felt guilty. Y'know, like I'd be cheating on Ross or something."
"No. Ross, it, it just seems that y'know it's time we-we y'know, move on. I mean, I mean don't' you think?"
"Ross, you got that for free from the museum gift shop."
"Well, oh, Mark, I'm doing this for the wrong reasons, y'know? I'm just doing it to get back at Ross. I'm sorry, it's not very fair to you."
"Oh wait, Ross, would you just stay and help me get dressed?"
"Ross! Stop that!"
"Rosss..."
"Ross, why didn't you tell me that?"
"Oh! Tommy, this is Ross. Ross, Tommy."
"Ross, would you just stop it! It's getting really old."
"Oh my God! Phoebe look, it's Ross and that girl."
"Ross gave it to me."
"Take it like a man, Ross!"
"All right! Ross, do you think it's easy for me to see you with somebody else?"
"Noo! Maybe! I, I don't know. Ross, I still can't forgive you for what you did, I can't, I just, but sometimes when I'm with you I just, I feel so..."
"What are you talking about, Ross, you just said that you read it twice! Look, y'know what, either it does or it doesn't, and if you have to even think about it..."
"You have! Ross, you should give yourself credit. I mean my Mom never thought this would work out. It was all, \"Once a cheater, always a cheater.\""
"I hate when Ross is right!"
"Ross, you guys went out once. You took your kids to Chucky Cheese, and you didn't even kiss her."
"Hi guys! This is Josh. Josh, these are my friends, and that's Ross."
"Ross, didn't you ah, play soccer in High School? Oh no wait, that's right. You just organized their game schedules on your Commodore 64."
"Huh. Well, then you'd better keep it away from Ross's hair. So this is pretty rare. How did you get that?"
"Ross, can you pass me the yams?"
"No! Wait! Wait-wait! Ross, please!"
"I'll be right there! Okay, Ross, please come on! I thought we have moved on! I thought we've gotten to a place where we could be happy for each other! I mean was that just me?"

"Well, I just checked our messages and Joshua didn't call. I mean you'd think he'd be worried about me not showing up at his club. Ugh, you know what makes it so much worse, Ross is all happy in Vermont!"
"Please, Ross, you-you got hurt playing badminton with my dad."
"Well, it was all Ross's idea."
"Oh, Ross, I'm sorry. I completely ruined your evening."

"Ross, that girl just spent the entire evening talking to your friends, asking to hear stories about you, looking through Monica's photo albums, I mean you don't do that if you're just in it for two weeks."

"Yeah, maybe, but I don't think I even care. I don't think he's the one I'm sad about. Y'know, I know that I said that I am totally okay with Ross getting married, but as it turns out, I don't think I'm handling it all that well."
"Well, yeah, y'know how Ross and I were on again, off again, on again, off again? I guess I just figured that somewhere down the road, we would be on again."
"Oh Ross, you're so great."
"Alright, fine, you go ahead and you do that, alright Ross."

"Ross do you realise this is the first time in my life I'm doing something I actually care about. This is the first time in my life I'm doing something that I'm actually good at. I mean. if you don't get that..."
"Oh my God. I cannot keep having this same fight over and over again, Ross, no, you're, you're, you're making this too hard."
"Come on Ross! You said you wanted to talk about it, let's talk about it!! How was she?"

"Ross, that girl just spent the entire evening talking to your friends, asking to hear stories about you, looking through Monica's photo albums, I mean you don't do that if you're just in it for two weeks."
"What's this? Is this Ross's wedding invitation?"
"Ross, hi, it's Rachel. I'm just calling to say that um, everything's fine and I'm really happy for you and your cat......I am over you. I am over you and that, my friend, is what they call closure."
"Oh my God. Oh my God Ross, no, hang up the phone, give me the phone Ross, give me the phone, give me the phone, give me the. . ."

"Yeah. It's just gonna be too hard. Y'know? I mean, it's Ross. How can I watch him get married? Y'know it's just, it's for the best, y'know it is, it's... Y'know, plus, somebody's got to stay here with Phoebe! Y'know she's gonna be pretty big by then, and she needs someone to help her tie her shoes; drive her to the hospital in case she goes into labour."
"Oh, well, actually we were just talking about me not going to Ross's wedding."
"Because, I can't! Ross, I told you, no. I can't."
"I'm just bummed about the way I left things with Ross. I shouldn't have lied to him about having to work. He seemed so mad at me."
"I'm not in love with Ross!"

"Phoebe, I'm going to Ross's wedding because he is my ex-boyfriend and that would be really uncomfortable. Not because, I'm still in love with him! I mean, hey, y'know, I like Ross as much as the next guy, y'know? Clearly I have feelings for him, but feelings don't mean love! I mean, I still have loving feelings for Ross. Yeah! But, I have, I have continuing feelings of love, but that doesn't mean that-that I'm still in love with him. Y'know? I-I have sexual feelings for him, but I do love him-Ohh! Oh my God! Oh my-why didn't you tell me?!!"
"You all know? Does Ross know?"
"Yeah, I have to tell Ross that I love him. Now honey, you take care, you don't have those babies until I get back."
"...And so then I realised. All this stuff I had been doing. proposing to Joshua, lying to Ross about why I couldn't come to the wedding. Was all just a way of..."
"Ross said my name up there, I mean, come on, I just can't pretend that didn't happen can I?"
"Whoa, wait, listen, I think I'm just gonna talk to Ross about what he think it meant."
"Ross said my name. Okay? My name."
"If anybody asks, I'm your sister, Joan. Listen. C'mon, you guys. Ross said my name up there that obviously means that he still loves me!"
"Well, Ross said my name."
"No, you're not an idiot, Ross. You're a guy very much in love."
"Oh, come on Ross! I think it would be really good for you!"
"Well-well, I don't know Ross-really?"

"All right. Woo! Hey, look at that, the airport's moving. Hey, are we moving?! Are we moving? Why are we moving? They said they were gonna wait! Miss? Yeah, does the captain know that we're moving? Oh my... Ross, you better be under the wheels of this thing!!"
"Ross said my name up there, I mean, come on, I just can't pretend that didn't happen can I?"
"Whoa, wait, listen, I think I'm just gonna talk to Ross about what he think it meant."
"Ross said my name. Okay? My name. Ross said my name up there that obviously means that he still loves me! Okay, don't believe me, I know I'm right-do you guys want to go downstairs and get a drink?"
"Well, Ross said my name."
"No, you're not an idiot, Ross. You're a guy very much in love."
"Oh, come on Ross! I think it would be really good for you!"
"Well-well, I don't know Ross-really?"
"Oh Ross, come on! You just did what you had to do."

"What?! I didn't have a good time in Greece! Ross abandoned me! Okay, I couldn't get a plane out, so I had to stay in their honeymoon suite with people coming up to me all the time going, \"Oh, Mrs. Geller, why are you crying?\" I mean, it was sooo humiliating. I felt like such an idiot! I mean, it's all my fault! And you know why, because I make very bad decisions."
"Yes it is! It is true! I went, I went after Ross in stupid London."
"Ohh, he's married! Ross is married. I can't-I still can't believe it."
"Y'know what Ross? You're not going anywhere. You're gonna sit right here. I'm gonna make you a cup of tea and we're gonna talk this thing whole out. All right? Hey, Dave!"

"Okay. Uhh, Ross, y'know what, there's something that I-that I have to talk to you about and everybody's saying that I shouldn't tell you, but I think they're wrong. I mean, and you know how people can be wrong."
"Okay, Ross, I'm really trying to tell you something here."
"Umm, okay, I think I'm-I'm just gonna-just gonna say it. Just gonna say it. Uhh, I'm still in love with you Ross."
"Ross, things aren't gonna be weird between us, right? I mean was that just the stupidest thing, me telling you that?"

"What? What are you talking about?! You-you're the one who's been telling me to get over Ross and move on. I'm moving on, and you're moving on with me. Come on, give me one good reason why you don't wanna go."

"Ross? Look, whatever this relationship stuff that Emily wants, just give it to her. Come on, the bottom line here is that you love her. So just fix whatever she wants fixed. Just do it. I mean, you're gonna have to try. You'll just gonna hate yourself if you don't. Oh come on answer it! It's driving me crazy!"
"Ohh! Lucky me! Oh my God! That is good news, Ross! I think that's the best news I've heard since Le Poo died!"
"Oh yeah, really? Is it Ross? Yeah? Okay, well let me make this a just a little bit easier for you."
"Look, I know you guys heard about the whole thing with me and Ross but y'know, I've been obsessing about it all day and I'd just love not to talk about it. All right?"
"That's not Ross!"

"Well, of course I am! It's not gonna happen to Ross! He's your brother. He's your old college roommate. Ugh, it was just a matter of time before someone had to leave the group. I just always assumed Phoebe would be the one to go."
"Oh, Ross..."
"Ross, I..."
"Ross, honey, is there anything we can do?"
"How's Ross doing? Y'know since all the Emily stuff."

"Oh, honey, please, no, I can't get started with all that Ross stuff again. I mean, he's gonna screwed up for a looong time. And besides y'know, I don't, I don't go for guys right after they get divorced."
"Ross couldn't fit down the trash chute."
"Ross! Janice?!"
"Yes, I know! And Joey knows! But Ross doesn't know so you have to stop screaming!!"
"Hey Ross! Any word on the apartment yet?"
"Oh Ross, honey you gotta stop torturing yourself!"
"Oh yeah! Oh my God! That is our friend! It's Naked Ross!"
"Well, Ross, we were worried about you. We didn't know how you were going to react."
"Hmm. Look, Ross, if you want your neighbors to like you, why don't you just pay the hundred bucks? The party's gonna cost you way more than that."
"Ross, honey, it's a nice couch. It's not a magic couch."
"Ross!"
"Ross!"
"Ross!! Oh my--ugh!! You kept count?! You are such a loser!"
"Ross, didn't you say that there was an elevator in here?"
"Hey! Joey, would you mind giving me and Ross a hand moving his couch?"
"Hey Ross! I brought reinforcements."
"Ross, I don't, I just don't think it's going to fit."
"I cannot believe Ross is buying this!"
"Ross! We broke up two years ago; you've been married since then. I think it's okay that we see other people."
"But y'know, I never really had anything to worry about. Ross was never very good at the flirting thing."
"No. No. Every thing's--they're fine. Great pizza. But it's uh, actually umm my friend Ross. He uh, just gets really nervous when he's flirting."
"Hey Ross? Umm, I just ran into Caitlin in the hallway and-and uh, you must be getting better at this flirting stuff than I thought."
"No honey, it's okay! Listen, I'll got to Ross's and get the blender, you get all the margarita stuff ready."
"Noo! Oh no! No! God no! He should not get back together with her. I know that! You know that! Even Ross knows that! But that still doesn't give us the right to erase his message!"
"Okay, just a little scared. What's going on Ross?"
"Okay, no, that's not the right decision. That's not, that's not right, no Ross-Ross, come on! I mean, that woman made you miserable! Okay, Ross, do you really want to get back into that?"
"Ugh, Ross! That was not a near death experience! That was barely an experience!"
"Ross! Come on! That's all right! Fine--Okay, I have a weird thing about my eye. Can we not talk about it please?"
"Ross! Stop it! Come on!"
"And um, what-what is that Ross?"
"Ohh wow! I'm sorry, but Ross you kicked off your shoes!"
"Okay umm, Ross? I'm-I'm really warm, so I'm going to be taking off my sweater. Now, I'm just letting you know that this is not an invitation to the physical act of love."
"No, I don't! Ross, I think I'm just a more secure person than you are."
"Ross! What are you... I'm sorry sir. I just, I think he just really likes you."
"Ross, I have been walking around like this since the plane! I can-you have so crossed a line."
"Ross, no! There is no way I am leaving this room looking like this!"
"Ross, I am a human doodle!!"
"No! Ross, come on! No! Listen, look I thought a lot about how to tell you this and the bottom line, Ross, is we can not stay married."
"Oh Ross, come on! This is not, this is not a marriage!! This is the world's worst hangover! Ross, listen, if you do not get this annulment, I will!"
"Ross, thank you. Hey, do you guys wanna go see a movie?"
"Ross, thank you. Hey, do you guys wanna go see a movie?"
"I would love to live with you Ross; that's-that's great! Thank you!"
"Ross-Ross, you have no idea what this means to me! I mean, I mean I was gonna be homeless. You just saved me! You're my hero!"
"Yeah. Y'know umm, uh, umm, about that, umm, Ross I really appreciate your offer to let me move in and everything, but don't you think it's gonna be weird?"
"Okay, but Ross, eventually you and I are gonna be dating."
"Ross, hey you know what might make it less boring?"
"Wow, that's great Ross, I'm sorry we weren't more supportive before."
"Yeah, I mean, come on Ross, no one will even notice. I mean they're probably not even listening!"
"Okay! \"Hello Ross, this is Dr. McNeeley from the Fake Accent University, we'd like you to come on board with us full time!"
"Ross got married again-Nooooooo!!!!!!!!!"
"Ross!! Are you crazy?! I am still your wife!! What, were you just never gonna tell me?!! What the hell is wrong with you?!!!! Ugh, I could just kill you!!!!"
"When?! After the birth of our first secret child?! Ross didn't get the annulment; we are still married."
"So, I still have boxes here. I still have boxes at Ross's, and I have nowhere to live! Wow. I could so easily freak out right now."
"Ross! Y'know what, I just got-why? Why did you do this?!"
"Well, y'know what? Thanks to you I'm half way there! Ugh! Oh! I am so mad! Ross, I don't think I have ever been this angry!"
"Ross, please, I found the magazines!"
"Ross! Your honor, rest assured relationship ended like two years ago! And could you strike \"Consummated like bunnies\" from the record?"
"Okay Ross, we're-wait a minute. Umm, I uh, I kinda have a little confession."
"Hey, thanks Ross, for taking care of all of this."
"Ohh, are you setting Ross up with someone? Does she have a wedding dress?"
"What's up, Ross?"
"Oh no. No Ross, don't do this."
"I thought this might happen today. Ross, I know the holidays can be rough. Y'know? And it's probably really hard for you to be alone right now."
"Yeah, but she also invited you and Ross. Yeah, honey, I'm sorry, but I don't think that was a romantic thing."
"Well, that's a lot better than Ross trying to kiss me in High School, and saying that he did it because he needed chapstick."
"Ross! Phoebe's gonna be here any second, she cannot see this!"
"Ross, get over it! It's not like she hates you."
"Ross, she's not weird, she just wants her stuff to be one of a kind."
"Well then honey, buy the lamp! Hey, we have that 60 bucks from Ross."
"And you know Monica and Ross!"
"No, of course, of course I've heard of them! Ross, what did you get?"
"With Ross and Jill?"
"With Ross and my sister?"
"With my sister Jill and my ex-boyfriend Ross?"

"Oh my God! I can not believe that! I mean I don't really like it when Ross goes out with anyone, but my sister isn't that like incest or something?! Oh my God, and they're gonna have sex! Oh! Oh no what if he marries her too?! Oh this is just terrible, this is just terrible. And I can't stop it! I can't-I don't own Ross! Y'know? And Jill, she should be able to do whatever it is that she wants to do! And oh my God, I can't believe Ross is marrying my little sister, this terrible. Oh my God, this is just the worst thing that could have ever happened to me."
"That is great. Hey, y'know who doesn't have to job hunt? Ross. He works at the university."
"Oh not-not so much. Umm, what-what do you, what do you mean is there something wrong with Ross?"
"No! No I, no Ross is not a geek!"
"What handsome is not your type? Smart? Kind? Good kisser? What those things aren't on your list? Ross is a great guy! You would be lucky to be with him!"
"Ross is on a date with my sister and they shut the drapes two and a-half-hours ago."
"Oh Ross, hi! Hey, how are ya? There you are!"
"No-no-no! No-no-no! Please Ross, I can't! I can't do it! It's just gonna freak me out!!!"
"Ross thanks."
"No honey, okay, okay, you wanna know why Ross canceled the date? Because I asked him to."
"Because you are my sister and Ross and I have this huge history..."
"Look, this is not that big of a deal! You just don't date Ross! There's a million other guys out there, you just..."
